      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/40/827",
      "text": [
        ": «لاَ بَأْسَ أَنْ يُصَلِّيَ أَحَدُكُمْ فِي اَلثَّوْبِ اَلْوَاحِدِ وَ أَزْرَارُهُ مَحْلُولَةٌ إِنَّ دِينَ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ حَنِيفٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.827 - Ziyad ibn Suqah narrated from Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) that He said: \"There is no issue if one of you prays in a single garment with its buttons undone. Indeed, the religion of Muhammad (sw) is upright (easy and straightforward).\""
        ]
      }
